explanation: The solution uses prefix XOR to efficiently calculate the XOR of all segments of size k. It then uses a count array to keep track of the frequency of each XOR value and finds the maximum number of segments with XOR equal to 0. The minimum number of changes required is then calculated as n - max_same.

